WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.250 --> 00:00:03.000
Previously on X-Men...

2
00:00:03.083 --> 00:00:06.583
My mom handed me over
to the Prime Sentinels.

3
00:00:06.667 --> 00:00:08.167
They collared me. What's left here?

4
00:00:08.875 --> 00:00:09.875
Me.

5
00:00:11.458 --> 00:00:13.138
Living doesn't get cheat codes.

6
00:00:14.208 --> 00:00:16.708
Life's a total risk and it's on you.

7
00:00:16.792 --> 00:00:18.500
Take it.

8
00:00:18.583 --> 00:00:20.333
You call yourselves a family?

9
00:00:20.625 --> 00:00:24.042
Humanity would rather die
than have kids like us.

10
00:00:24.125 --> 00:00:27.458
Missile alert!
Missile alert! Missile alert!

11
00:00:29.375 --> 00:00:31.333
Jubilee!

12
00:00:33.542 --> 00:00:35.292
The sky is on fire.

13
00:00:35.375 --> 00:00:37.917
Leaders are working fast
to avert this mutant doomsday.

14
00:00:39.333 --> 00:00:42.042
Those rebel leaders
I told you about in the future.

15
00:00:42.125 --> 00:00:44.750
rambling about the adventures
of the X-Men.

16
00:00:44.833 --> 00:00:48.042
those legends really didn't
do my folks justice.

17
00:00:48.125 --> 00:00:49.958
Goodbye. son.

18
00:01:25.167 --> 00:01:27.792
Move! School's right up ahead.

19
00:01:32.542 --> 00:01:34.333
What direction now?

20
00:01:34.417 --> 00:01:36.042
It's over there.

21
00:01:51.875 --> 00:01:53.333
What?

22
00:01:54.375 --> 00:01:56.333
No. no.

23
00:01:56.417 --> 00:02:00.250
What did I tell you? The X-Men are dead
and they're never coming back.

24
00:02:00.333 --> 00:02:01.583
Ferme ta guele!

25
00:02:01.667 --> 00:02:04.333
Or I'll spare our ears
any more of your lip.

26
00:02:04.417 --> 00:02:06.792
We need to split up.
regroup somewhere safe.

27
00:02:06.875 --> 00:02:10.333
Safe? This was the safe place
for kids like us.

28
00:02:10.417 --> 00:02:11.476
Don't move!

29
00:02:11.500 --> 00:02:13.083
This area's restricted.

30
00:02:13.167 --> 00:02:15.167
Oh. please. don't hurt us.

31
00:02:16.375 --> 00:02:18.708
Don't worry. son. we won't hurt you.

32
00:02:18.792 --> 00:02:21.125
We're definitely the good guys.

33
00:02:23.333 --> 00:02:25.917
They call themselves "X-Factor."

34
00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:29.542
The US Government's mutant task force
charged with containing global crises

35
00:02:29.625 --> 00:02:31.125
in a world without the X-Men.

36
00:02:31.208 --> 00:02:35.042
With unprovoked violence
against mutant youths on the rise.

37
00:02:35.125 --> 00:02:38.750
Director Val Cooper is under fire
for a controversial campaign

38
00:02:38.833 --> 00:02:42.708
to relocate mutants. quote.
"for their own safety."

39
00:02:43.208 --> 00:02:45.417
Tão fácil.

40
00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:47.583
That's three times in a row.

41
00:02:49.250 --> 00:02:50.583
Dinner's on me.

42
00:02:50.667 --> 00:02:53.333
I'm starting to get the hang
of this video game stuff.

43
00:02:53.417 --> 00:02:55.125
Come on. Wanna play?

44
00:02:55.208 --> 00:02:56.750
The X-Men wouldn't be playing around.

45
00:02:56.833 --> 00:02:59.292
while the Government's
detaining mutant kids.

46
00:02:59.375 --> 00:03:02.250
It doesn't help that Forge and Bishop
disappeared on us.

47
00:03:02.333 --> 00:03:05.792
They'll pop up sooner or later. I promise.

48
00:03:05.875 --> 00:03:08.292
And until then.
the whole world's upside down

49
00:03:08.375 --> 00:03:10.708
and we're just plugging quarters
at the arcade.

50
00:03:10.792 --> 00:03:13.625
Jeez. aren't you supposed to be
the peppy one?

51
00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:20.792
Cable?

52
00:03:22.250 --> 00:03:24.542
Just to get this straight.

53
00:03:24.625 --> 00:03:27.708
you want me. Jubilee.

54
00:03:27.792 --> 00:03:32.167
to be part of your...
super-secret black ops team?

55
00:03:33.833 --> 00:03:35.083
I'm working on a case.

56
00:03:35.167 --> 00:03:36.417
And you just happen to be

57
00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:39.167
one of the last people
to cross paths with my target.

58
00:03:40.833 --> 00:03:42.500
Apocalypse?

59
00:03:42.583 --> 00:03:44.250
He's been off the grid for a while.

60
00:03:44.333 --> 00:03:47.167
But now one of his Horsemen's
re-emerged on the scene.

61
00:03:47.250 --> 00:03:49.417
Goes by the name of War.

62
00:03:49.500 --> 00:03:50.875
I've been raiding his safe houses.

63
00:03:50.958 --> 00:03:53.958
trying to figure out what
that psychopath's cooking up.

64
00:03:54.042 --> 00:03:55.268
Just turn on the news.

65
00:03:55.292 --> 00:03:58.000
A perfect time for Apocalypse
to ignite his dream war

66
00:03:58.083 --> 00:03:59.708
between humanity and mutants.

67
00:03:59.792 --> 00:04:02.917
His sole aim is to dominate
the evolutionary chain.

68
00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:05.542
If he's not stopped.
he'll wipe out most of the world

69
00:04:05.625 --> 00:04:08.667
and enslave anyone
unlucky enough to survive.

70
00:04:08.750 --> 00:04:10.958
Sounds like a lot of not fun.

71
00:04:11.625 --> 00:04:13.542
You're telling me.

72
00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:16.042
Listen close.

73
00:04:16.125 --> 00:04:17.750
This is dangerous work.

74
00:04:17.833 --> 00:04:20.625
I got no need for students or heroes.

75
00:04:20.708 --> 00:04:22.292
We are soldiers.

76
00:04:22.375 --> 00:04:25.583
Once you're in. you're in.
No questions. no retreat.

77
00:04:25.667 --> 00:04:26.917
Governments will hunt us.

78
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:29.500
Nowhere will be safe.

79
00:04:30.333 --> 00:04:34.708
But it beats playing video games
while the world's going to hell.

80
00:04:36.583 --> 00:04:38.583
This team got a name?

81
00:05:56.375 --> 00:05:58.083
Mission's simple. team.

82
00:05:58.167 --> 00:06:01.292
We find Apocalypse's Horseman.
we find Apocalypse.

83
00:06:02.542 --> 00:06:05.208
Psylocke. see what you can read.

84
00:06:05.792 --> 00:06:07.917
You picked quite the week
for a duck shoot.

85
00:06:11.292 --> 00:06:14.167
Too many minds.
I can't isolate any of them.

86
00:06:14.792 --> 00:06:16.250
Warren. how's the view from the sky?

87
00:06:18.375 --> 00:06:20.042
No sign.

88
00:06:20.125 --> 00:06:21.750
I'm heading farther north.

89
00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:25.708
Jubilee. Sunspot.
what's with the dancing?

90
00:06:25.792 --> 00:06:27.125
This isn't date night.

91
00:06:27.208 --> 00:06:28.958
Didn't you say "Blend in"?

92
00:06:29.917 --> 00:06:31.500
Unlike that guy.

93
00:06:31.583 --> 00:06:33.542
Green skin. bowl cut.

94
00:06:35.708 --> 00:06:38.500
It's our target. On my 12 o'clock.

95
00:06:38.583 --> 00:06:40.417
Tail him but keep your distance.

96
00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:43.167
Genocides. massacres. civil wars.

97
00:06:43.250 --> 00:06:47.042
Guy's got more blood on his hands
than history books can count.

98
00:06:51.333 --> 00:06:52.583
Cable. we lost him.

99
00:06:52.667 --> 00:06:54.083
Anyone got eyes from above?

100
00:06:54.167 --> 00:06:55.917
He's making for an alleyway up north.

101
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.958
He's on to us. I need backup now.

102
00:07:01.500 --> 00:07:04.458
What the...

103
00:07:04.542 --> 00:07:06.500
Don't let War get away.

104
00:07:13.458 --> 00:07:15.167
I might know a short cut or two.

105
00:07:15.250 --> 00:07:17.083
"Might" isn't exactly reassuring.

106
00:07:17.167 --> 00:07:18.417
Just wait for my signal.

107
00:07:24.083 --> 00:07:25.250
Now!

108
00:07:31.417 --> 00:07:35.167
Whoo! X-Force 1.
Creepy Apocalypse Zombies 0.

109
00:07:52.917 --> 00:07:54.417
Sweet dreams.

110
00:08:00.958 --> 00:08:03.500
You fight a battle
that cannot be won.

111
00:08:03.583 --> 00:08:06.875
Against the dawn of an age
that cannot be stopped.

112
00:08:07.583 --> 00:08:12.167
"When He-Who-Never-Dies
will cull the weak from the herd."

113
00:08:12.250 --> 00:08:14.458
"Until only the strong survive."

114
00:08:14.542 --> 00:08:16.250
Yes. we know.

115
00:08:16.333 --> 00:08:18.875
You forsake your master. heretic.

116
00:08:19.458 --> 00:08:23.083
But in due time.
you will face his judgment.

117
00:08:25.292 --> 00:08:26.708
He won't speak willingly.

118
00:08:26.792 --> 00:08:29.125
Apocalypse made loyal servants of us all.

119
00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:40.625
I thought telepaths were supposed to...

120
00:08:40.708 --> 00:08:42.042
Have manners?

121
00:08:42.125 --> 00:08:44.583
That might be how your professor did it

122
00:08:44.667 --> 00:08:46.267
but we don't have time for pleasantries.

123
00:08:48.833 --> 00:08:50.958
Well done. well done.

124
00:08:51.042 --> 00:08:53.083
Well done. War.

125
00:08:54.167 --> 00:08:55.375
Open it.

126
00:08:56.667 --> 00:09:00.750
Soon the Old World shall finally pass away

127
00:09:00.833 --> 00:09:04.958
and together we shall forge a new one

128
00:09:05.042 --> 00:09:08.583
in Fire and Blood!

129
00:09:08.667 --> 00:09:11.667
His mind's booby-trapped.

130
00:09:11.750 --> 00:09:13.875
Like a wall of diamonds blocking me.

131
00:09:13.958 --> 00:09:15.583
I stole as much as I could.

132
00:09:19.833 --> 00:09:22.792
Put him out of his misery
before he hurts anyone else.

133
00:09:22.875 --> 00:09:24.125
Whoa. what?

134
00:09:24.208 --> 00:09:26.958
War is a Horseman.
He cannot be saved.

135
00:09:27.042 --> 00:09:29.792
-You were.
-Yes. by Rogue.

136
00:09:29.875 --> 00:09:31.208
And now she's gone.

137
00:09:31.292 --> 00:09:35.000
Trust me. Jubilee. this isn't murder.

138
00:09:35.083 --> 00:09:36.667
It's mercy.

139
00:09:40.250 --> 00:09:42.542
But we could call the authorities.

140
00:09:42.625 --> 00:09:43.875
He might have more to say.

141
00:09:51.500 --> 00:09:53.667
We are the authority.

142
00:10:05.750 --> 00:10:07.792
You didn't have to kill him back there.

143
00:10:07.875 --> 00:10:09.708
We could have gotten more out of him.

144
00:10:09.792 --> 00:10:12.417
Last I checked.
I give the orders around here.

145
00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:15.434
And last I checked. we were
trying to stop a ruthless mass murderer.

146
00:10:15.458 --> 00:10:17.292
not steal from his playbook.

147
00:10:17.375 --> 00:10:19.125
I helped you get the Horseman.

148
00:10:19.208 --> 00:10:22.792
But if you want anything else.
I'm gonna need a little less killing.

149
00:10:22.875 --> 00:10:24.958
Take it that means you've got a hunch.

150
00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:29.208
Psylocke said the Horseman's mind
was blocked by a psychic wall.

151
00:10:29.292 --> 00:10:31.500
and saw diamonds.

152
00:10:31.583 --> 00:10:35.083
I know only one telepath
who's got a thing for diamonds.

153
00:10:35.792 --> 00:10:37.542
Saw her turn into one in Genosha.

154
00:10:39.083 --> 00:10:40.875
Emma Frost.

155
00:10:42.333 --> 00:10:44.708
Well. what do we have here?

156
00:10:45.417 --> 00:10:49.042
A stray. a firecracker and a pit-bull.

157
00:10:51.500 --> 00:10:52.583
Not gonna lie.

158
00:10:52.667 --> 00:10:54.875
If X-Force is going to crash my party.

159
00:10:54.958 --> 00:10:57.792
that dashing Warren Worthington
is more my type.

160
00:10:57.875 --> 00:11:00.083
Though I wouldn't mind making you bark.

161
00:11:00.167 --> 00:11:01.333
-Woof.
-Ew.

162
00:11:01.417 --> 00:11:04.458
Your exploits in Rio
spun up a lot of chatter.

163
00:11:04.583 --> 00:11:06.750
You all are quite the party crashers.

164
00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:08.042
We're wasting time.

165
00:11:08.125 --> 00:11:10.708
The X-Men saved your life
in Genosha.

166
00:11:10.792 --> 00:11:13.167
As well as their heroic image. And?

167
00:11:13.250 --> 00:11:16.250
You owe us. We need information.

168
00:11:16.792 --> 00:11:18.417
We all have wants.

169
00:11:18.500 --> 00:11:20.958
Some of us can just afford them
more easily.

170
00:11:23.042 --> 00:11:26.125
Believe you and bowl-cut
were business partners.

171
00:11:26.208 --> 00:11:29.667
You want to tell us a little
about the nature of that business?

172
00:11:32.583 --> 00:11:34.583
Oh. you're serious?

173
00:11:35.417 --> 00:11:37.500
And you're terrified.

174
00:11:37.583 --> 00:11:40.333
Listen. my dears. I'm a matchmaker.

175
00:11:40.417 --> 00:11:43.083
I help demand meet supply
and take a small cut.

176
00:11:43.167 --> 00:11:44.625
I don't get curious.

177
00:11:44.708 --> 00:11:46.417
So please pack up your blame and...

178
00:11:46.500 --> 00:11:48.042
Just tell us what the Horseman wanted.

179
00:11:48.708 --> 00:11:50.917
He needed to smuggle cargo
into Switzerland.

180
00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:52.208
Got an address?

181
00:11:52.333 --> 00:11:54.750
Of course.

182
00:11:55.750 --> 00:11:58.333
But as I said.

183
00:11:58.417 --> 00:11:59.708
I'm in it for a cut.

184
00:11:59.792 --> 00:12:02.750
So where shall we start the bidding?

185
00:12:17.833 --> 00:12:18.875
Horsemen tech.

186
00:12:18.958 --> 00:12:22.333
Everything Apocalypse needs to convert
mutants into his loyal death squad.

187
00:12:22.417 --> 00:12:24.750
No. Cable. this equipment.

188
00:12:24.833 --> 00:12:28.500
it's far more advanced
than any he ever used on me.

189
00:12:30.083 --> 00:12:31.625
The crates are empty.

190
00:12:31.708 --> 00:12:34.667
If Apocalypse was here. he's long gone.

191
00:12:36.958 --> 00:12:39.625
Whatever Apocalypse
is working on.

192
00:12:39.708 --> 00:12:42.167
it's already built and moved out.

193
00:12:42.250 --> 00:12:45.333
Bastard no doubt staged the Rio attack
to pull our focus.

194
00:12:45.417 --> 00:12:47.667
You led us to a dead end.

195
00:12:47.750 --> 00:12:49.958
Not dead. but an end?

196
00:12:50.042 --> 00:12:51.162
Yes.

197
00:12:53.750 --> 00:12:55.417
X-Factor.

198
00:13:01.833 --> 00:13:03.000
Drop your weapons.

199
00:13:03.083 --> 00:13:05.583
By order of the United States Government.

200
00:13:05.667 --> 00:13:08.042
-You really are a total...
-Sorry.

201
00:13:08.125 --> 00:13:11.417
In these times. amnesty is everything.

202
00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:13.458
You've got two options.

203
00:13:13.542 --> 00:13:16.417
Stand down or be put down.

204
00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:20.542
Unlike you.
X-Force doesn't answer to anyone.

205
00:13:20.625 --> 00:13:22.917
Least of all. Uncle Sam's mutant lapdogs.

206
00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:24.625
Traitors!

207
00:13:33.875 --> 00:13:36.708
Don't bring a gun to a fist-fight.

208
00:13:38.167 --> 00:13:41.500
Well done. But I only need one of me.

209
00:13:58.458 --> 00:13:59.500
Yawn.

210
00:14:00.708 --> 00:14:02.208
Eat this. big guy!

211
00:14:03.292 --> 00:14:04.458
Polaris. help!

212
00:14:08.167 --> 00:14:09.333
Wrap this up.

213
00:14:17.625 --> 00:14:19.875
Polaris. what are you doing?

214
00:14:19.958 --> 00:14:21.792
We're not the bad guys here.

215
00:14:21.875 --> 00:14:23.375
It's not about good or bad.

216
00:14:23.458 --> 00:14:26.083
It's about authority.
And you don't have any.

217
00:14:26.167 --> 00:14:28.208
I'm an X-Man trying to help.

218
00:14:28.292 --> 00:14:29.583
X-Men. remember them?

219
00:14:29.667 --> 00:14:31.292
Ya used to be one.

220
00:14:31.375 --> 00:14:32.708
You're not an X-Man.

221
00:14:32.792 --> 00:14:35.542
You're on a secret assassination
hit squad.

222
00:14:35.625 --> 00:14:37.000
You don't understand.

223
00:14:37.083 --> 00:14:39.458
You have no idea the danger coming.

224
00:14:39.542 --> 00:14:41.042
Release us!

225
00:14:42.792 --> 00:14:44.392
Move! Move to the jet!

226
00:14:46.292 --> 00:14:49.417
Jubilee! No!

227
00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:51.417
Move it. or we're toast.

228
00:14:51.500 --> 00:14:53.667
Get off me! We have to go back for her.

229
00:14:56.375 --> 00:15:00.542
Come on. The guy left you high and dry
without a second thought.

230
00:15:00.625 --> 00:15:02.958
I mean. do you really
wanna take the fall for this?

231
00:15:04.375 --> 00:15:07.292
Just tell us what Cable's up to
and where he's going.

232
00:15:07.375 --> 00:15:10.167
Jubilee. I'm sure you didn't mean
to get caught up in all of this.

233
00:15:10.250 --> 00:15:11.708
You're just a kid.

234
00:15:13.917 --> 00:15:16.000
Look. X-Factor
was formed by the Government

235
00:15:16.083 --> 00:15:19.583
to legally police threats.
mutant and human.

236
00:15:19.667 --> 00:15:22.167
We're just trying to keep order
by easing tensions.

237
00:15:22.250 --> 00:15:24.417
Help us help you.

238
00:15:24.500 --> 00:15:26.625
You mean help you
round up mutants?

239
00:15:26.708 --> 00:15:29.208
That's your plan for easing tensions?

240
00:15:29.292 --> 00:15:31.958
With the violent bigots
who are attacking us?

241
00:15:32.042 --> 00:15:35.083
You guys are gonna have to bring in
a telepath 'cause I'm not talking.

242
00:15:35.167 --> 00:15:37.000
You have one of those
on your C-list roster?

243
00:15:37.083 --> 00:15:38.542
Knock-off Cyclops?

244
00:15:39.167 --> 00:15:41.125
Maybe give us a minute. Alex.

245
00:15:41.208 --> 00:15:43.375
I'll do better than that.
I'll give you two.

246
00:15:45.375 --> 00:15:48.792
This is who you left the X-Men
to work with?

247
00:15:48.875 --> 00:15:52.500
I could say the same for you.
working for a vigilante merc like Cable.

248
00:15:52.583 --> 00:15:56.167
Okay. his methods are definitely
a little questionable.

249
00:15:56.250 --> 00:15:57.333
I'm working on that.

250
00:15:57.417 --> 00:15:59.458
But at least he's on a mission
worth fighting for.

251
00:15:59.542 --> 00:16:01.542
Sorry I can't say the same for you.

252
00:16:01.625 --> 00:16:04.167
We've all lost a lot. Jubilee.

253
00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:06.667
I was a foster kid
when the Professor took me in.

254
00:16:07.167 --> 00:16:08.958
The X-Men became my family too.

255
00:16:09.542 --> 00:16:12.833
Now they're gone
and you and I are all that's left.

256
00:16:13.708 --> 00:16:16.417
We're all doing our best to honor them.

257
00:16:16.500 --> 00:16:18.167
If the Professor was here.

258
00:16:18.250 --> 00:16:20.917
do you think he'd be proud
of what you're doing?

259
00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:23.667
Heck. I'm wondering
if he'd be proud of me.

260
00:16:24.667 --> 00:16:26.833
Got a fresh cell for ya. hotshot.

261
00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:45.800
Why do we have to stay here?

262
00:17:08.458 --> 00:17:09.851
We're going back for Jubilee.

263
00:17:09.875 --> 00:17:12.750
Relax. Da Costa.
I'm buying us time to regroup.

264
00:17:13.208 --> 00:17:15.792
Your girl can handle her own
against the mutant mall cops.

265
00:17:15.875 --> 00:17:17.625
What if she can't?

266
00:17:17.708 --> 00:17:20.042
Look. I've trained you both.
She'll be fine.

267
00:17:20.125 --> 00:17:21.542
We need to stay on the trail

268
00:17:21.625 --> 00:17:25.000
and find Apocalypse and
his Frankenstein machine before...

269
00:17:25.083 --> 00:17:27.875
We'll finish the mission.
but not at the cost of our own.

270
00:17:27.958 --> 00:17:29.833
That's not what the X-Men would have done.

271
00:17:29.917 --> 00:17:32.000
Yeah. and look where that got 'em.

272
00:17:32.083 --> 00:17:33.917
She can handle it on her own.

273
00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:38.625
Just because she can do it alone
doesn't mean she should have to.

274
00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:41.375
Mmm...

275
00:17:48.125 --> 00:17:49.583
Come to salt the wound?

276
00:17:54.542 --> 00:17:57.792
Call it payback for reminding me
what I'm in this for.

277
00:17:58.500 --> 00:18:00.500
I can buy you five minutes.

278
00:18:00.583 --> 00:18:03.000
How you use them. that's up to you.

279
00:18:11.583 --> 00:18:13.292
Come on.

280
00:18:28.708 --> 00:18:31.750
♪ Tell me. tell me
what you really want from me ♪

281
00:18:31.833 --> 00:18:35.167
♪ You've got to let me know ♪

282
00:18:35.250 --> 00:18:39.125
♪ I'm falling off
and I need you terribly ♪

283
00:18:39.208 --> 00:18:42.375
♪ One down and one to go ♪

284
00:18:59.000 --> 00:19:00.640
Come in. It's Jubilee. Over.

285
00:19:01.208 --> 00:19:02.333
Can anyone hear me?

286
00:19:02.417 --> 00:19:03.542
Jubes. where are you?

287
00:19:03.625 --> 00:19:05.000
It's cool.

288
00:19:05.458 --> 00:19:08.250
I'm fine. I broke out.

289
00:19:08.333 --> 00:19:11.208
But I've got additional cargo and
I'm definitely gonna need backup.

290
00:19:11.292 --> 00:19:13.667
Cargo? What cargo?

291
00:19:17.125 --> 00:19:20.625
♪ Way to go. way to flip off everyone ♪

292
00:19:20.750 --> 00:19:21.809
Come on.

293
00:19:21.833 --> 00:19:23.375
get to the flight deck. That way.

294
00:19:23.917 --> 00:19:26.292
Land on the south deck
and pick up the kids.

295
00:19:26.375 --> 00:19:27.792
Jubes. what about you?

296
00:19:29.750 --> 00:19:30.792
I'll be fine.

297
00:19:30.875 --> 00:19:32.625
Look alive. team.

298
00:19:38.792 --> 00:19:42.250
♪ I bounce back and I run some more ♪

299
00:19:43.125 --> 00:19:46.625
♪ But this is it
I'm giving up. I'm calling quits ♪

300
00:19:46.708 --> 00:19:50.125
♪ So get down and meet me on the floor ♪

301
00:19:50.458 --> 00:19:52.917
♪ Way to go. way to flip off everyone ♪

302
00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:55.667
Hold it right there.
We got you.

303
00:19:55.750 --> 00:19:58.000
Call for backup.

304
00:19:59.167 --> 00:20:00.847
Hey! What are you doing?

305
00:20:03.125 --> 00:20:04.559
Rogue mutants on the loose.

306
00:20:04.583 --> 00:20:06.792
Requesting X-Factor immediately.

307
00:20:06.875 --> 00:20:09.708
Just follow my lead.
I'm gonna get us out of here.

308
00:20:09.792 --> 00:20:10.958
Wait for my signal.

309
00:20:12.333 --> 00:20:13.667
Go!

310
00:20:13.750 --> 00:20:16.250
♪ Go ♪

311
00:20:22.833 --> 00:20:27.167
♪ Volcano girls. we really can't be beat ♪

312
00:20:27.250 --> 00:20:30.333
♪ Warm us up and watch us blow ♪

313
00:20:30.417 --> 00:20:33.708
♪ But now and then we fail
and we admit defeat ♪

314
00:20:33.792 --> 00:20:37.000
♪ We're falling off. we are watered down
and fully grown ♪

315
00:20:41.042 --> 00:20:43.125
♪ 'Cause I don't wanna go ♪

316
00:20:43.208 --> 00:20:46.292
♪ Leave me lying here ♪

317
00:20:46.375 --> 00:20:50.292
♪ 'Cause I don't wanna go ♪

318
00:21:08.292 --> 00:21:09.708
Hold it right there!

319
00:21:10.542 --> 00:21:11.750
Your choice.

320
00:21:13.917 --> 00:21:15.708
It doesn't have to go this way.

321
00:21:18.583 --> 00:21:19.833
Sure doesn't.

322
00:21:19.917 --> 00:21:21.833
Peace out. losers!

323
00:21:21.917 --> 00:21:25.167
♪ 'Cause I don't wanna go ♪

324
00:21:44.500 --> 00:21:46.458
That team's gonna be a problem.

325
00:21:46.542 --> 00:21:49.333
What happened? Where's Jubilee?

326
00:21:49.417 --> 00:21:52.542
Escaped. Any idea how that happened?

327
00:21:54.292 --> 00:21:58.833
X-Force's blatant acts of rebellion
will not be tolerated.

328
00:21:59.458 --> 00:22:00.917
But rest assured.

329
00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:04.542
X-Factor is here to protect
humans and mutants.

330
00:22:04.625 --> 00:22:08.375
And we will not rest until
these fugitives are brought to justice

331
00:22:08.458 --> 00:22:12.292
and prosecuted
to the full extent of the law.

332
00:22:13.167 --> 00:22:14.875
A lot of heat on us.

333
00:22:14.958 --> 00:22:16.375
Congrats. team.

334
00:22:16.458 --> 00:22:20.000
Being national fugitives should really
help us stay under the radar.

335
00:22:20.083 --> 00:22:21.875
We did what needed to be done.

336
00:22:21.958 --> 00:22:23.958
Perhaps. but at what cost?

337
00:22:24.042 --> 00:22:25.875
Less than the cost of doing nothing.

338
00:22:25.958 --> 00:22:29.292
If we're not going to defend the world
Apocalypse wants to destroy.

339
00:22:29.375 --> 00:22:31.375
what's the point of even fighting him?

340
00:22:32.583 --> 00:22:34.542
Hey. you all holding up okay?

341
00:22:34.625 --> 00:22:35.875
-Yeah.
-I know this has been...

342
00:22:35.958 --> 00:22:38.833
She's right. you know.
But Apocalypse is still out there.

343
00:22:38.917 --> 00:22:41.917
Where we're going.
it's no place for a bunch of kids.

344
00:22:43.042 --> 00:22:44.042
Trust me.

345
00:22:45.042 --> 00:22:47.083
Kids are tougher than you think.

346
00:23:05.792 --> 00:23:08.125
Field computer operational. Greetings.

347
00:23:08.792 --> 00:23:11.375
Nathan. everything all right?

348
00:23:11.458 --> 00:23:13.667
Yeah. I'm good.

349
00:23:15.333 --> 00:23:18.125
We should probably get word
to the rest of the Askani.

350
00:23:18.208 --> 00:23:20.375
Let them know to make their way here.

351
00:23:20.458 --> 00:23:24.250
And I think it's way past due
you get to grill your mother and me.

352
00:23:24.333 --> 00:23:26.917
I'm sorry. Nathan. I have to object.

353
00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:29.583
You must send the X-Men
back to their time.

354
00:23:29.667 --> 00:23:31.542
No. not yet.

355
00:23:32.458 --> 00:23:33.875
I don't want 'em to go.

356
00:23:33.958 --> 00:23:37.458
I'm sorry. Apocalypse's defeat here
is only the beginning.

357
00:23:37.542 --> 00:23:41.125
Shadows gather in the past
where history is still unwritten.

358
00:23:41.208 --> 00:23:45.167
If the X-Men do not return.
there may be no future left to protect.

359
00:23:45.250 --> 00:23:47.375
What about protecting my son?

360
00:23:47.458 --> 00:23:50.500
You can't expect us
to just leave him here.

361
00:23:50.583 --> 00:23:52.375
And yet you must.

362
00:23:52.458 --> 00:23:55.125
But you can take heart knowing
he will be protected.

363
00:23:55.208 --> 00:23:56.875
By people who care for him.

364
00:23:56.958 --> 00:23:59.750
Please. we just need more time.

365
00:23:59.833 --> 00:24:02.750
Now. we must be strong. Nathan.

366
00:24:03.625 --> 00:24:05.875
To do what they cannot.

367
00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:09.250
Such is the burden of destiny.

368
00:24:10.375 --> 00:24:11.875
And children.

369
00:24:26.167 --> 00:24:30.625
Computer. time-slide the X-Men.

370
00:24:34.042 --> 00:24:35.375
I love you. son.

371
00:24:35.458 --> 00:24:36.833
Goodbye. Nathan.
